gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 118, Nuggets 117
gameRecap.excerpt: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander made a go-ahead bucket with 0.9 seconds left as the Thunder held on and defeated the Nuggets, 118-117. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led the Thunder with 25 points, six rebounds, and eight assists as Jalen Williams (24 points) and Chet Holmgren (17 points, 11 rebounds, nine blocks) totaled 41 points. Nikola Jokic led Denver with 24 points and 12 assists while Michael Porter Jr. added 20 points and 11 rebounds. The Thunder snapped the Nuggets 3-game win streak and improve to 16-8 on the year as the Nuggets move to 17-10.
